Iulius Frontinus, author of the extant treatises ‘de aquaeductis' and ‘ strategematon,' praet. urb. A. D. 70 (H. 4. 39, 1). He must have been cos. before he was legatus of Britain; and Borghesi infers from an inscription in which only the letters ‘ on ' survive (see Klein, Fasti) that he was cos. im- mediately after Cerialis (see on c. 8, 2) in July A. D. 74. But this would show Britain to have been some months with- out a legatus, and it is more probable that he was cos. earlier, and succeeded Cerialis in Britain early in A. D. 74.
